issue.body:
- Feature for issue https://github.com/uber/ludwig/issues/1028
- There is a pretrained model with `n` number of features, and the current model has `n+1` number of features. Load weights from the pretrained model onto the current model.

@w4nderlust this PR is not meant to be the final PR, but I wanted to show if this is the way you would like to go forward. Please suggest changes in terms of API. Currently, I have modified the `train` method.  I will add the tests once the overall idea is approved.

body:
Hi @jenishah, thanks for posting your tip. This is a bit outdated but do you happen to remember where `model.get_weights()`and `model.set_weights()` can be modified? I'm having trouble finding them. 

@w4nderlust thank you for such amazing attention to your users! Any guidance on how to transfer trained model weights to a new model with a new dataset's model definition (such as transfer learning)?

Thanks in advance.

@w4nderlust thanks for the prompt response man. @dantreiman 's work looks very interesting, I look forward to seeing the solution here. I'll probably have some questions with regards to the argument inputs and CLI implementation (if that's not being too demanding for this feature.)

Either way, thank you for the effort and update as I know this feature involves a bit of digging and refactoring.

Cheers.
